sentence: Consumer shares were mixed ahead of the opening bell Tuesday.
In consumer stocks news, food and beverage company Dean Foods Company ( DF ) has been downgraded by Morgan Stanley to an underweight rating from equalweight.
The firm also cut its price target on the stock to $17 from $19 a share.
Shares in the company were flat at $18.68 pre-bell.
This is towards the upper end of the stock's 52 week trading range between $14.56 and $19.74.
The Children's Place Retail Stores ( PLCE ), a specialty apparel retailer, reported Tuesday its Q3 2015 net income higher than the Street consensus, while revenues fell short.
Shares in the company were unchanged at $48.76 pre-bell.
This is towards the lower end of the stock's 52 week trading range between $46.74 and $69.90.
And Home Depot ( HD ) Tuesday reaffirmed its sales and EPS guidance for fiscal 2015, and set out financial targets for years through fiscal 2018.
For FY 2015, the home improvement retailer affirmed sales to increase 5.7%, with comps of 4.9%.
The Street consensus is a 4.9% increase in comps.
Shares in the company were 0.6% lower at $133.19 pre-bell.
This is towards the upper end of the stock's 52 week trading range between $92.17 and $135.47.
